El Golfo, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain. El Golfo is a unique volcanic crater on the island of Lanzarote in the Canary Islands, Spain. The emerald green color of the water in the crater is caused by the high concentration of algae and other organisms in the lake. The water is a stunning shade of green and contrasts beautifully with the deep blue of the Atlantic Ocean.
